Snow and heavy winds to affect Romania until Friday evening
Romanian weather officials announced on Wednesday that snow and wind will intensify across the country starting February 23, 11 p.m. until Friday, 18 p.m.It will temporarily snow in most of Romania during the period. Snow will be more intense in South Romania on Wednesday night and Thursday morning, then it will intensify in the Eastern parts of the country. Wind is expected to exceed 50 km per hour in the counties of Constanta, Tulcea, Galati, Braila, Ialomita and Calarasi in South and South East Romania in the first part of the period.